.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::DVM \- NIP\-90 Data Vending Machine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::DVM;
\&
\&    # Job request (kind 5000\-5999)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::DVM\->job_request(
\&        pubkey => $hex_pubkey,
\&        kind   => 5001,
\&        inputs => [[\*(Aqhttps://example.com/audio.mp3\*(Aq, \*(Aqurl\*(Aq]],
\&        output => \*(Aqtext/plain\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Job result (kind 6000\-6999)
\&    my $result = Net::Nostr::DVM\->job_result(
\&        pubkey  => $hex_pubkey,
\&        request => $event,
\&        content => \*(AqTranscribed text here.\*(Aq,
\&        amount  => \*(Aq5000\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Job feedback (kind 7000)
\&    my $feedback = Net::Nostr::DVM\->job_feedback(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        request_id => $job_request_id,
\&        customer   => $customer_pubkey,
\&        status     => \*(Aqprocessing\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse any DVM event
\&    my $parsed = Net::Nostr::DVM\->from_event($event);
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->validate($event);
\&
\&    # Kind helpers
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->is_job_request(5001);   # true
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->is_job_result(6001);    # true
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->is_job_feedback(7000);  # true
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->result_kind(5001);      # 6001
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->request_kind(6001);     # 5001
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-90 (Data Vending Machine). Nostr acts as a marketplace
for data processing where customers request jobs and service providers
compete to fulfill them. Three event kind ranges are used:
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBJob Request\fR (kind 5000\-5999) \- Published by a customer
to request data processing. Contains input data, expected output
format, optional parameters, a bid amount, and preferred relays
and service providers. All tags are optional.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBJob Result\fR (kind 6000\-6999) \- Published by a service
provider with the output of processed data. The kind is always
1000 higher than the corresponding request kind. References the
original request event and includes the customer\*(Aqs pubkey.
.IP \(bu 4
\&\fBJob Feedback\fR (kind 7000) \- Published by a service
provider to communicate status updates. Status values include
\&\f(CW\*(C`payment\-required\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`processing\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`success\*(C'\fR, and
\&\f(CW\*(C`partial\*(C'\fR. MAY include partial results in content.
.PP
Job requests support encrypted parameters via the \f(CW\*(C`encrypted\*(C'\fR tag.
When encrypted, input and param tags are encrypted with the service
provider\*(Aqs key using NIP\-04 and placed in the content field.
.SH CONSTANTS
.IX Header "CONSTANTS"
.SS SP_DISCOVERY_KIND
.IX Subsection "SP_DISCOVERY_KIND"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = Net::Nostr::DVM::SP_DISCOVERY_KIND;  # 31990
.Ve
.PP
NIP\-89 kind for service provider discoverability announcements.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 3
\&    my $dvm = Net::Nostr::DVM\->new(
\&        status => \*(Aqprocessing\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::DVM\*(C'\fR object. Croaks on unknown arguments.
Array fields (\f(CW\*(C`inputs\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`params\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`providers\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`hashtags\*(C'\fR) default to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS job_request
.IX Subsection "job_request"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::DVM\->job_request(
\&        pubkey    => $hex_pubkey,                      # required
\&        kind      => 5001,                             # required (5000\-5999)
\&        inputs    => [[$data, $type, $relay, $marker], ...], # optional (i tags)
\&        output    => $mime_type,                        # optional
\&        params    => [[$key, $value], ...],             # optional (param tags)
\&        bid       => $millisats,                       # optional
\&        relays    => [$url, ...],                      # optional
\&        providers => [$pubkey, ...],                   # optional (p tags)
\&        hashtags  => [$tag, ...],                      # optional (t tags)
\&        encrypted => 1,                                # optional
\&        content   => $encrypted_payload,               # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a job request Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`kind\*(C'\fR must be in the
5000\-5999 range. Input types are \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`job\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`text\*(C'\fR.
When \f(CW\*(C`encrypted\*(C'\fR is set, an \f(CW\*(C`encrypted\*(C'\fR tag is added and content
should contain the NIP\-04 encrypted parameters.
.SS job_result
.IX Subsection "job_result"
.Vb 9
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::DVM\->job_result(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,      # required
\&        request    => $request_event,   # required (Net::Nostr::Event)
\&        content    => $payload,         # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        relay_hint => $relay_url,       # optional
\&        amount     => $millisats,       # optional
\&        bolt11     => $invoice,         # optional
\&        encrypted  => 1,               # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a job result Net::Nostr::Event. The kind is automatically
set to the request kind + 1000. The \f(CW\*(C`request\*(C'\fR tag contains the
stringified JSON of the original request. When \f(CW\*(C`encrypted\*(C'\fR is set,
input tags from the request are omitted to avoid leaking clear text.
.SS job_feedback
.IX Subsection "job_feedback"
.Vb 12
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::DVM\->job_feedback(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,      # required
\&        request_id => $event_id,        # required (e tag)
\&        customer   => $customer_pubkey, # required (p tag)
\&        status     => $status,          # required
\&        extra_info => $description,     # optional
\&        relay_hint => $relay_url,       # optional
\&        amount     => $millisats,       # optional
\&        bolt11     => $invoice,         # optional
\&        content    => $partial_result,  # optional, defaults to \*(Aq\*(Aq
\&        encrypted  => 1,               # optional, adds \*(Aqencrypted\*(Aq tag
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 7000 job feedback Net::Nostr::Event. Valid status
values: \f(CW\*(C`payment\-required\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`processing\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`success\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`partial\*(C'\fR.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $dvm = Net::Nostr::DVM\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a DVM event (kind 5000\-5999, 6000\-6999, or 7000) into a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::DVM\*(C'\fR object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for unrecognized kinds.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-90 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not in 5000\-5999, 6000\-6999, or 7000
.IP \(bu 4
Job result missing \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`request\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Job feedback missing \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag
.PP
Returns 1 on success.
.SS is_job_request
.IX Subsection "is_job_request"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->is_job_request(5001);  # true
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the kind is in the 5000\-5999 range.
.SS is_job_result
.IX Subsection "is_job_result"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->is_job_result(6001);  # true
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the kind is in the 6000\-6999 range.
.SS is_job_feedback
.IX Subsection "is_job_feedback"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::DVM\->is_job_feedback(7000);  # true
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the kind is 7000.
.SS result_kind
.IX Subsection "result_kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $rk = Net::Nostr::DVM\->result_kind(5001);  # 6001
.Ve
.PP
Returns the result kind for a given request kind (request + 1000).
.SS request_kind
.IX Subsection "request_kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $rk = Net::Nostr::DVM\->request_kind(6001);  # 5001
.Ve
.PP
Returns the request kind for a given result kind (result \- 1000).
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS inputs
.IX Subsection "inputs"
Arrayref of arrayrefs from \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags. Each contains
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$data, $type, $relay, $marker]\*(C'\fR. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS output
.IX Subsection "output"
Expected output MIME type from \f(CW\*(C`output\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS params
.IX Subsection "params"
Arrayref of arrayrefs from \f(CW\*(C`param\*(C'\fR tags. Each contains
\&\f(CW\*(C`[$key, $value]\*(C'\fR. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS bid
.IX Subsection "bid"
Maximum payment amount in millisats from \f(CW\*(C`bid\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS relays
.IX Subsection "relays"
Arrayref of relay URLs from \f(CW\*(C`relays\*(C'\fR tag. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS providers
.IX Subsection "providers"
Arrayref of service provider pubkeys from \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS hashtags
.IX Subsection "hashtags"
Arrayref of hashtag strings from \f(CW\*(C`t\*(C'\fR tags. Defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR.
.SS encrypted
.IX Subsection "encrypted"
True if the event has an \f(CW\*(C`encrypted\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS request_id
.IX Subsection "request_id"
Job request event ID from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag (results and feedback).
.SS request_event
.IX Subsection "request_event"
Stringified JSON of the original request from \f(CW\*(C`request\*(C'\fR tag (results).
.SS relay_hint
.IX Subsection "relay_hint"
Relay hint from \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS customer
.IX Subsection "customer"
Customer pubkey from \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag (results and feedback).
.SS amount
.IX Subsection "amount"
Payment amount in millisats from \f(CW\*(C`amount\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS bolt11
.IX Subsection "bolt11"
Bolt11 invoice from \f(CW\*(C`amount\*(C'\fR tag.
.SS status
.IX Subsection "status"
Feedback status from \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR tag. One of \f(CW\*(C`payment\-required\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`processing\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`success\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`partial\*(C'\fR.
.SS extra_info
.IX Subsection "extra_info"
Extra human\-readable info from \f(CW\*(C`status\*(C'\fR tag.
